design_brief_for_codex.gui_change_appform_template_substitution:
Extend AppForm.tsx click handler to support `{fieldId}` placeholder substitution in `button.event.value` when value is a string. Pseudo-code: ```ts
const rawValue = button.event?.value;
let emittedValue: unknown = rawValue ?? values;
if (typeof rawValue === 'string') {
  emittedValue = rawValue.replace(/\{(\w+)\}/g, (_match, fieldId) => {
    const fieldValue = values[fieldId];
    return fieldValue !== undefined && fieldValue !== '' ? String(fieldValue) : '';
  });
}
onWidgetEvent({ event: 'onFormSubmit', key: button.event?.key || 'onFormSubmit', value: emittedValue });
```. Behaviour: if button.event.value is a string with `{fieldId}` placeholders, substitute each with the current form value (empty string if missing). If button.event.value is a non-string (object/array) or undefined, preserve existing behaviour exactly.

design_brief_for_codex.ops_change_render_step_widget_trees:
After the gui change merges and redeploys, update each render_* step in repos/ops/automation/agents/travel/runtime.yaml to append an app:form widget to its widget tree. Append AS the last child of the existing app:column. The form's fields are pre-populated from the current classify_intent values via Jinja, and the submit button emits a templated travel command. Per intent, the field/template is:

  render_flights:
    fields: [
      {id: 'origin',         title: 'Origin (IATA)',      default_value: '{{ classify_intent.origin | default("SFO") }}'},
      {id: 'destination',    title: 'Destination (IATA)', default_value: '{{ classify_intent.destination | default("JFK") }}'},
      {id: 'departureDate',  title: 'Departure date',     default_value: '{{ classify_intent.departureDate | default("2026-07-15") }}'},
      {id: 'adults',         title: 'Adults',             default_value: '{{ classify_intent.adults | default(1) }}'}
    ]
    button: {text: 'Refine search', colorType: 'primary',
             event: {key: 'command', value: 'travel flights from {origin} to {destination} on {departureDate} for {adults} adults'}}

  render_hotels:
    fields: [
      {id: 'cityCode',       title: 'City (IATA)',        default_value: '{{ classify_intent.cityCode | default("NYC") }}'},
      {id: 'departureDate',  title: 'Check-in date',      default_value: '{{ classify_intent.departureDate | default("2026-08-15") }}'}
    ]
    button: {text: 'Refine search', colorType: 'primary',
             event: {key: 'command', value: 'travel hotels in {cityCode} on {departureDate}'}}

  render_locations:
    fields: [
      {id: 'keyword',        title: 'Keyword',            default_value: '{{ classify_intent.keyword | default("Boston") }}'}
    ]
    button: {text: 'Refine search', colorType: 'primary',
             event: {key: 'command', value: 'travel locations near {keyword}'}}

  render_activities:
    fields: [
      {id: 'keyword',        title: 'Place or landmark',  default_value: '{{ classify_intent.keyword | default("Times Square") }}'}
    ]
    button: {text: 'Refine search', colorType: 'primary',
             event: {key: 'command', value: 'travel activities near {keyword}'}}

  render_amadeus_failure:
    fields: same as the original intent's form (introspect classify_intent.intent and pick the matching field set in the render python step). Button text: 'Try again with new values'.

  render_help: optional — could include a quick-pick form pre-loaded with example queries. Skip for this round to keep diff small.
